ShortName: LDA, QDA & naive Bayes
Topic: statistical-learning
Concepts: Bayes' theorem as a classification recipe (flip class-conditional density into a posterior),
 LDA (shared covariance gives a linear decision boundary),
 QDA (per-class covariance gives a curved decision boundary),
 naive Bayes (independence assumption drops the covariance matrix entirely),
 estimating priors from class frequencies,
 the flexibility dial from LDA to QDA (bias-variance trade-off in number of parameters)
BuildsOn: [multivariate-normal-distribution](multivariate-normal-distribution/lesson.qmd),
 [classification-evaluation](classification-evaluation/lesson.qmd),
 [priors-posteriors-and-updating](priors-posteriors-and-updating/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
